      "content": "Actually, stopping early is the most dangerous mistake you can make because it gives surviving bacteria the perfect chance to mutate into a super-resistance monster that no one else can treat. You might feel fine today, but within weeks or months you could end up with a condition that doctors literally have no more effective drugs for. It is far better to endure these few days of harmless chemicals than to gamble your entire life expectancy on \"feeling better.\"",
      "source": "target",
